  "prompt": "Is spray paint waterproof?",
  "response": "Spray paint itself is not inherently waterproof, although it can be highly water-resistant. The water resistance of spray paint can depend on various factors including the type of paint (e.g., acrylic, enamel), the surface it is applied to, and how well it is cured and sealed. For projects requiring waterproofing, applying a clear waterproof sealant over the spray paint can enhance its ability to withstand moisture and prolong its longevity.",
